Text Fields #!N #!EC #!N #!N Many of the dialog boxes 
in Data Explorer include text fields that you can change. You 
can place a text cursor in the box by clicking on 
the box. With the cursor in the box, you can use 
the keyboard to alter the text. The number of times you 
click on the text box depends on how you want to 
edit it: #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Single Click 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Places the text cursor at the point on 
which you clicked in the existing text field. All text you 
type is then inserted in the field, after the selected point. 
You can also use the Delete and Backspace keys. #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Double Click #!EF #!I50 #!N Places the text cursor 
at the start of the word on which you clicked in 
the existing text field, and highlights that word. When you type, 
the highlighted text is replaced with the new text you enter. 
Pressing the Backspace key deletes the highlighted text. #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Triple Click #!EF #!I50 #!N Highlights the entire text field. 
When you type, the entire field is replaced with the new 
text you enter. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Drag #!EF #!I50 #!N 
Highlights the portion of the text field that you drag the 
cursor over. When the mouse button is released, the text remains 
highlighted. Typing anything replaces the highlighted text with what you type; 
pressing the Backspace key deletes the highlighted text. #!I0 #!N #!N 
#!N #!N Data Explorer allows you to copy and paste text 
within text fields. To copy text, select the desired text by 
double-clicking, triple-clicking, or dragging the cursor over it with the left 
mouse button. This action selects and copies the text. To paste 
the selected text in a text field, position the mouse cursor 
at the point you want to insert the text, and click 
on the center mouse button. The pasted text is inserted at 
the mouse cursor position. #!N #!N If the amount of text 
entered into a text field cannot be fully displayed, you can 
use the keyboard to scroll the cursor through the text. Pressing 
the left or right arrow key moves the cursor one character 
to the left or right, respectively. Also, pressing the Control key 
(  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl #!EF ) at the same time as either 
the left or right arrow key moves the cursor one  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   
word #!EF to the left or right, respectively. The Home key 
will move the cursor to the beginning of the text field. 
The End key will move the cursor to the end of 
the text field. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
